When one child class inherits from only one parent class, it is known as single inheritance.

Class A  (Base Class / Parent Class / Super Class)

              ↑  Inherited by

Class B  (Child Class / Sub Class / Derived Class)

Example:

class Animal {
    void eat() {
        System.out.println("eating...");
    }
}

class Dog extends Animal {
    void bark() {
        System.out.println("barking...");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        Dog d = new Dog();
        d.bark();
        d.eat();
    }
}

Output:
barking...
eating...

In this example, `Dog` class inherits the `Animal` class — single inheritance.

